\section{Getting Started}

\subsection{System Requirements}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Browser:} Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Edge 90+, Safari 14+
    \item \textbf{Webcam:} 720p minimum (1080p recommended)
    \item \textbf{Microphone:} Built-in or external microphone
    \item \textbf{Internet:} Stable connection, minimum 2 Mbps upload speed
    \item \textbf{OS:} Windows 10+, macOS 10.15+, Linux (Ubuntu 18.04+)
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Creating an Account}
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Navigate to \url{https://interviewmate-ai.com}
    \item Click \textbf{``Get Started''} or \textbf{``Sign Up''}
    \item Fill in your details:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Full Name
        \item Email Address (valid email required)
        \item Password (min 8 chars, 1 uppercase, 1 number)
        \item College/University Name
        \item Branch/Department
        \item Academic Year
    \end{itemize}
    \item Click \textbf{``Create Account''}
    \item Verify your email via the confirmation link
\end{enumerate}

\begin{tcolorbox}[tipbox]
Use your college email if available for better profile matching with campus placement requirements.
\end{tcolorbox}

\section{Dashboard Overview}

After logging in, you'll see your \textbf{Personal Dashboard} with:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \faChartLine\ \textbf{Performance Overview:} Your latest scores and trends
    \item \faCalendarAlt\ \textbf{Recent Sessions:} History of past mock interviews
    \item \faTrophy\ \textbf{Achievements:} Milestones and badges earned
    \item \faBullseye\ \textbf{Quick Start:} Buttons to start a new interview
\end{itemize}

\section{Starting a Mock Interview}

\subsection{Step 1: Interview Setup}
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Click \textbf{``Start New Interview''} from the dashboard
    \item Select your \textbf{Job Category} (e.g., Software Development, Data Science)
    \item Select your \textbf{Target Company} (optional - for company-specific questions)
    \item Upload your \textbf{Resume} (PDF or DOCX, max 5MB)
    \item Configure settings:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Number of questions (5-20)
        \item Time per question (1-5 minutes)
        \item Difficulty level (Easy, Medium, Hard, Mixed)
    \end{itemize}
    \item Click \textbf{``Begin Interview''}
\end{enumerate}

\begin{tcolorbox}[infobox]
The AI analyzes your resume to generate personalized questions based on your skills and experience.
\end{tcolorbox}

\subsection{Step 2: Pre-Interview Check}
Before starting, the system will:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Test your webcam and show a preview
    \item Test your microphone and audio levels
    \item Check your internet connection speed
    \item Verify adequate lighting conditions
\end{itemize}

\begin{tcolorbox}[warnbox]
Ensure you are in a well-lit, quiet room. Poor lighting affects facial emotion analysis accuracy.
\end{tcolorbox}

\subsection{Step 3: During the Interview}
The interview interface shows:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Top Bar:} Question number, timer, pause button
    \item \textbf{Center:} Current question text
    \item \textbf{Left:} Your video feed with real-time emotion indicators
    \item \textbf{Right:} Live transcript of your speech
    \item \textbf{Bottom:} Recording controls and real-time tips
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Real-time Tips:} The AI provides suggestions like:
\begin{itemize}
    \item ``Try to maintain more eye contact with the camera''
    \item ``You seem nervous - take a deep breath''
    \item ``Speak slower for better clarity''
    \item ``Good! Your confidence is improving''
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Step 4: Answering Questions}
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Read the question carefully
    \item Click \textbf{``Start Recording''} when ready
    \item Answer using the STAR method (Situation, Task, Action, Result)
    \item Click \textbf{``Submit Answer''} when done
    \item Review the AI-generated STAR model answer for reference
    \item Click \textbf{``Next Question''} to continue
\end{enumerate}

\section{Understanding Your Report}

After completing the interview, you'll receive a \textbf{Comprehensive Confidence Report}:

\subsection{Score Breakdown}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Facial Emotion Score (0-100):} Measures confidence, engagement, and nervousness from facial expressions
    \item \textbf{Speech Emotion Score (0-100):} Analyzes tone, stress, and enthusiasm in your voice
    \item \textbf{Clarity Score (0-100):} Evaluates speech pace, filler words, and pronunciation
    \item \textbf{Answer Quality Score (0-100):} Assesses relevance, grammar, and STAR compliance
    \item \textbf{Eye Contact Score (0-100):} Measures how well you maintained eye contact with the camera
    \item \textbf{Overall Confidence Score (0-100):} Weighted average of all factors
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Improvement Tips}
The report includes personalized suggestions:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Specific areas to improve (e.g., ``Reduce filler words like `um' and `uh''')
    \item Practice exercises tailored to your weak areas
    \item Recommended resources and tutorials
\end{itemize}

\section{Progress Tracking}

Navigate to \textbf{``My Progress''} to view:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Score Trends:} Line chart showing scores over time
    \item \textbf{Skill Radar:} Visual comparison of all skill areas
    \item \textbf{Session History:} Detailed log of all past interviews
    \item \textbf{Comparison:} How you rank against average users
\end{itemize}

\section{Exporting Reports}

To download your report:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Go to \textbf{``My Reports''} from the dashboard
    \item Select the session you want to export
    \item Click \textbf{``Export as PDF''}
    \item The PDF includes all charts, scores, and improvement tips
\end{enumerate}

\section{Troubleshooting}

\begin{tabular}{@{}p{4cm}p{8cm}@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Issue} & \textbf{Solution} \\
\midrule
Webcam not detected & Check browser permissions, ensure no other app is using the camera \\
Audio not recording & Check microphone permissions, test with another app \\
Low confidence scores & Practice in better lighting, speak clearly, maintain eye contact \\
Questions too hard/easy & Adjust difficulty in interview setup \\
PDF export fails & Check internet connection, try again after a few minutes \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}

\section{Privacy \& Data Security}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Video recordings are processed in real-time and not permanently stored
    \item Audio is transcribed and then deleted from servers
    \item All data is encrypted in transit (TLS 1.3) and at rest (AES-256)
    \item You can request data deletion from Profile Settings
\end{itemize}

